State.Author: C3pa
State.Description: Animates item pickup from the game world. This change adds more juice to the game and makes picking up items more satisfying. Inspired by a similar feature in Borderlands 2.
State.Name: Animated Pickup

State.Author: Hemaris
State.Description: Vivec and Molag Mar no longer look like empty water on the global map.
State.Name: Cantons on the Global Map

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Dropped items and corpses are automatically positioned and oriented to align with the ground.
State.Name: Just Drop It

State.Author: Vengyre
State.Description: MWSE-lua magic overhaul. Features reworked spell chances, reworked spell costs, Illusion effects overhaul, unique effect formulas, advanced multi-effect spell formula, effect synergies, spell rebalance, unique spells, reworked experience gain, Magicka Expanded integration. Many features are customizable.
State.Name: Magicka of the Third Era - MWSE-lua Magic Overhaul

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Adds a cancel button to Temple shrines and Imperial Cult altars.
State.Name: No Thank You

State.Author: Tamriel Rebuilt Team
State.Description: Tamriel Rebuilt is a fan project working to build the mainland of Morrowind Province in The Elder Scrolls III: Morrowind, while preserving the original game’s creative vision and direction.
State.Name: Tamriel Rebuilt

State.Author: Danae Aurel
State.Description: Modular versions of WARES for Vvardenfell, Tamriel Rebuilt, Skyrim Home of the Nords, and Province Cyrodiil including items, traders, npcs, Hold it and containers.
State.Name: Wares Ultimate

State.Author: Danae Merlord
State.Description:
100+ classes (vanilla, NPC classes, TR classes, new classes) that get a specific set of items and/or spells and powers as well as MWSE skill buffs. specifically tailored to your class. 

Loadouts include vanilla, TR, OAAB, and, depending on your modlist, **items from your mods.**

Includes custom classes
State.Name: Ahead of the Classes

State.Author: MOP Team
State.Description: Greatly improves performance and fixes tons of mesh errors.
State.Name: Morrowind Optimization Patch

State.Author: TES3 Community
State.Description: Patch for Purists is an unofficial patch for The Elder Scrolls III: Morrowind Game of the Year Edition which attempts to continue where the latest official version of the game left off. Over 9000+ bugs still present in the game have been fixed.
State.Name: Patch for Purists

State.Author: Merlord and XeroFoxx
State.Description: Adds new skooma mechanics including animated skooma pipe smoking, psychedelic shaders and sound effects, and skooma addiction.
State.Name: Skoomaesthesia

State.Author: Cross-Project Coordination
State.Description: Culminating from a year of hard work, Tamriel_Data contains a data unified file structure spearheaded by Project Tamriel and Tamriel Rebuilt as the first adopter.
State.Name: Tamriel_Data

State.Author: The AATL Team
State.Description: Tamrielic Lore is a book in vanilla Morrowind that describes various artifacts seen throughout Morrowind. An Addendum to Tamrielic Lore seeks to expand upon Morrowind's artifacts list, while adding more quests, items, and artifacts that reflect previous TES titles. This is the resource page for AATL, which contains all new resources used in AATL.
State.Name: AATL Data - An Addendum to Tamrielic Lore Data

State.Author: Apel
State.Description: Fire retexture mode for Morrowind.
State.Name: Apel's Fire Retexture

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Survival mod with hunger, thirst, tiredness, cooking, camping, crafting and temperature mechanics, and new visuals, from seeing frost on your breath in cold weather, watching your food cook on the grill in real time, and seeing your camping gear displayed dynamically on your backpack.
State.Name: Ashfall - A Camping Survival and Needs Mod

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Learn songs from other bards. Book performances with innkeepers. 38 songs to learn. New 'Performance' skill. Dynamic replacement of vanilla lutes with equippable versions.
State.Name: Bardic Inspiration

State.Author: abot
State.Description: Avoid actors getting stuck while opening doors
State.Name: Doors Anti Stuck

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk and Merlord
State.Description: This mod makes it so that the class images you see during character creation and when leveling up are specific to your class. No more recycling the vanilla image for custom classes!
State.Name: Dynamic Class Images

State.Author: Stuporstar and Greatness7
State.Description: Now works with OpenMW! MWSE Graphic Herbalism harnesses the power of lua and mesh switchnodes, allowing this mod to be run without an esp or standard scripts. This dramatically optimizes performance compared to older graphic herbalism mods. It also comes with an mod configuration menu to allow you to change settings.
State.Name: Graphic Herbalism - MWSE and OpenMW Edition

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Adds a feature-rich painting mechanic to Morrowind, letting you create paintings of in-game scenery that exist not just in the game as objects but are also saved as high-res images on your PC so you can use them outside the game.
State.Name: Joy of Painting

State.Author: OperatorJack and RedFurryDemon
State.Description: A lua-based framework for creating new, fully functional magic effects. Currently adds 109 new magic effects.
State.Name: Magicka Expanded

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: OAAB_Data is a free-to-use asset repository for the Morrowind Community.
State.Name: OAAB_Data

State.Author: Project Atlas Team
State.Description: The goal of Project Atlas is to identify the most performance heavy areas of vanilla Morrowind and some popular mods and target high usage/strain meshes in those areas for atlasing. This effort involves reworking the UVs for those meshes and creating texture atlases to cover various sets.
State.Name: Project Atlas

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Skills Module is a framework for MWSE+Lua mods that allows you to easily create new skills in Morrowind with just a few lines of code. Leveling and UI are handled automatically, with new skills added seamlessly into the stats menu.
State.Name: Skills Module

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: The Crafting Framework is library that allows modders to quickly and easily implement complex crafting mechanics in Morrowind.
State.Name: The Crafting Framework

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Allows your to tame and breed guars, and keep them as companions. Intelligent command menu gives unprecedented control over your guar. Attack enemies, fetch items, harvest plants etc. Build trust over time by keeping them happy and healthy to unlock more commands. Fight and play games to level up your guar.
State.Name: The Guar Whisperer

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Expands UI functionality with searching, filtering, and more visual feedback.
State.Name: UI Expansion

State.Author: Merlord Greatness7 MelchiorDahrk
State.Description: Adds a fishing mechanic with over 25 species of fish and dynamic fishing animations.
State.Name: Ultimate Fishing

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Implements more accurate, context-dependent tooltip displays for weapon damage and armor ratings, using MWSE-lua.
State.Name: Accurate Tooltip Stats

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Drip adds Diablo 2 style loot to Morrowind. Unique weapons, armor, clothing and accesories are dynamically generated, with over a hundred unique modifiers and more than a million possible combinations. Chance to apply modifiers configurable in the MCM.
State.Name: DRIP - Dynamic Randomised Item Properties

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: This mod changes how saves are handled by Morrowind. The goal of the mod is to provide more types of autosaves, as well as a rotating list of quicksaves/autosaves so that the player always has a save to go back to.
State.Name: Sophisticated Save System

Original.Meta:
[General]
gameName=Morrowind
gameFile=Data Files\Sound\Vo\Misc\Dagoth Ur Welcome C.mp3
Original.Name: Data Files_Sound_Vo_Misc_Dagoth Ur Welcome C.mp3

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description:
Introduces a backstabbing mechanic - do more damage when stabbing an enemy from behind (based on Agility/Sneak). Mod Configuration Menu includes option for Short Blades only or all weapons. Be warned - NPCs can backstab you as well!





Uses the latest development version of MWSE, not OpenMW compatible.
State.Name: Brutal Backstabbing

State.Author: Celediel
State.Description:
Guards with some actual spatial awareness! 



An MWSE-Lua mod that replicates Inquisitive Guards by RubberMan and Protective Guards by Fliggerty. Guards that catch the player sneaking about in town will follow them for a length of time dependent on their sneak skill and will come to the aid of an unwanted player who is attacked unprovoked
State.Name: More Attentive Guards

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Holding down a hotkey (default left shift) while clicking an item in your inventory will equip that item instead of picking it up. Uses MWSE+Lua.
State.Name: Quick Equip

State.Author: abot
State.Description:
Ammo autoequip while bow/crossbow/thrown weapon readied. It will remember and prefer last hand-picked ammo if pressing Alt while equipping it.

requires latest MWSE-Lua dev
State.Name: Smart Ammo

State.Author: Greatness7
State.Description: Adds animation blending to Morrowind, enabling smooth transitions between animations.
State.Name: Animation Blending

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Alternate Start and chargen overhaul. Over 60 scenarios. Chargen process streamlined and re-ordered. Fully customise your character or randomise everything.
State.Name: Chargen Scenarios

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Select from 27 different backgrounds, each with their own unique effects.
State.Name: Merlord's Character Backgrounds

State.Author: ModManSam
State.Description:
Add reputation gain to Fighters Guild, Imperial Legion and Thieves Guild quests.



Most faction questlines reward you with reputation, but it's mysteriously missing from the fighter's guild, imperial legion and thieves guild. This mod aims to rectify this oversight.
State.Name: Reputation Fixes

Original.Meta:
[General]
gameName=Morrowind
gameFile=Data Files\Sound\Vo\Misc\Dagoth Ur Welcome D.mp3
Original.Name: Data Files_Sound_Vo_Misc_Dagoth Ur Welcome D.mp3

State.Author: abot
State.Description: Avoid actors getting stuck while opening doors
State.Name: Doors Anti Stuck

State.Author: Half11
State.Description: This mod fixes Bethesda's overly enthusiastic expansion hooks by delaying the Dark Brotherhood attacks (for Tribunal) and limiting intrustive dialogue topics to a few NPCs (Bloodmoon).
State.Name: Expansion Delay

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: This mod aims to fix some inconsistencies with how leveled creatures are spawned.
State.Name: Less Lame Leveled Spawns

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: This mod provides one simple feature: any menu can be exited by right clicking. This includes dialog and barter menus, any service menus, as well as the main menu, save/load menu etc.
State.Name: Right Click Menu Exit

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: This simple mod provides an in-game HUD element as the game approaches critical memory limits.
State.Name: Memory Monitor

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Just some patches.
State.Name: Null's Minor Patches

State.Author: rfuzzo
State.Description: This mod adds compare tooltips for looked-at or equipped items against the equipped item of the same category. The mod has multiple MCM options to configure the comparison style.
State.Name: MWSE Compare Tooltips

State.Author: abot
State.Description: Makes companions (the ones with the short companion local variable set to 1) able to interact with possible loot sources and doors you Alt+Activate, can fix/improve some companions/followers features, detect abot's modded Scenic Travelling and apply it to followers not already compatible with it...
State.Name: Smart Companions

State.Author: Petethegoat
State.Description: Lets you randomise your race, appearance, class, and birthsign.
State.Name: Randomised Chargen

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Have issues with the game crashing on exit? This might help!
State.Name: Expeditious Exit

State.Author: Publicola and Spammer
State.Description: Read skill books as soon as you find them.
State.Name: Reading Is Good

State.Author: abot
State.Description: This mod gives you two ways you can know the closest Intervention spell destination.
State.Name: Smart Intervention

State.Author: Merzasphor
State.Description: This mod fixes a bug where GMST values are not applied properly when raising a skill via NPC training or a skill book.
State.Name: Skill Increase GMST Fix

State.Author: ZackHasACat
State.Description: Changes propylon index to be marked as keys, allowing them to be detected by "Detect Key" spells or effects.
State.Name: Detect Propylon Indices

State.Author: mort
State.Description: A fully customizable leveling mod that removes the level-up screen entirely. Never worry about min/maxing skill ups ever again. The functionality of GCD/MADD, but fully customizable and conflict-free. Play how you want, and leave leveling to the MULE.
State.Name: MULE - Mort's Ultimate Leveling Experience

State.Author: Hrnchamd
State.Description: Adds interactive placement, rotation and wall mounting of items. Arrange gear, books and anything else you can pick up. Requires MWSE 2.1.
State.Name: Perfect Placement

State.Author: helswake
State.Description: NPCs will not shout at you as often when you walk by. (Sets the GMST iGreetDistanceMultiplier to 4.)
State.Name: Greet Distance Reducer

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Automatically hides your drugs so you don't have to dump them on the floor in order to trade. Uses MWSE, no plugin required.
State.Name: MWSE Hide the Skooma

State.Author: Storm Atronach
State.Description: Adds an actual security skill check to disarming traps. Finally those Grandmaster probes will be useful!
State.Name: Actual Security Checks for Traps

State.Author: NullCascade and Zackhasacat
State.Description: Enables picking up books by default, instead of opening them. This can be disabled by holding shift. The behavior can be inverted using the mod config menu.
State.Name: Book Pickup

State.Author: Spammer
State.Description: Adds chances for the DRIP mod to drop items increasing custom skills added by Skills Module mod
State.Name: Drippified Skills Module - MWSE

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: This module makes it so that when the player or the player's companions are attacked, any companions will launch into action in defense.
State.Name: Diligent Defenders

State.Author: Virnetch
State.Description: Expands the vanilla Quick Menu by adding different hotkeys for holding or double tapping a button and/or when holding a specific button. All hotkeys use the same keys as in vanilla. In total there can now be 81 different hotkeyed items/spells. Requires MWSE 2.1
State.Name: Hotkeys Extended

State.Author: Half11
State.Description: The Publicans fixes several places in the vanilla game that were set up like inns (where you can rent rooms), but Bethesda still needed to add the option to rent a room.
State.Name: The Publicans

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Allows soultrap to make more intelligent use of available soul gems, including soul displacement and relocation. Includes optional leveling requirements.
State.Name: Smarter Soultrap

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Shows you which dungeons have been cleared in the tooltip and map menu.
State.Name: Been There Done That

State.Author: Virnetch
State.Description: Allows highlighting and hiding quests in the Journal questlist. Shift-Click on a quest to highlight it, Shift-Click again to hide and Shift-Click a third time to return to normal.
State.Name: Better Questlist

State.Author: abot
State.Description: Avoid actors getting stuck while opening doors
State.Name: Doors Anti Stuck

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Carries over unique item information, such as condition and script data when enchanting items.
State.Name: Consistent Enchanting

State.Author: Spammer
State.Description:
Picture this: You are in a middle of a fight, swinging a bound longsword, when suddenly it vanishes right from your hand. The cast time is up, and because you had no idea how much time you had left, you're now defenseless against your opponnents!

 Frustrating, isn't it?

 This mod intends to give you a visual idea of how much time you stil
State.Name: Effects Timers - MWSE

State.Author: abot
State.Description: Adds "Give" and "Take" buttons to any suitable actor/container, so you can easily move (all/all filtered) things in and out with Lua speed.
State.Name: Give or Take

Original.Name: Patch for More Attentive Guards v1.2-55897-1-2-1738349298.7z

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Just some patches.
State.Name: Null's Minor Patches

State.Author: abot
State.Description:
Lava and similar scripted damage sources should use fire damage instead.

More realistic and also a fire atronach will no more die walking in lava.
State.Name: Hot Lava

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Keep track of what books you have read by showing a "(Read)" indicator next to their names. You can also see a list of previously read books in the MCM menu.
State.Name: Book Worm

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Activate a scrib to pet it. It'll do a little butt thump.
State.Name: Pet the Damn Scrib
